node.text: Watch from just 2.9 miles away as Falcon 9 climbs to orbit at 9:06am this morning. This was one of the loudest launches I’ve heard, and one of the clearest I’ve seen, in recent memory.

node.title: Video: Falcon 9 launches the fourth Starlink mission

node.text: MiG-29 with @rookisaacman piloting and @drsianproctor in the backseat performs a pop break left at the end of a beautiful sunset and blue hour flight yesterday. Shot looking up out of an L-39 cockpit 🤙

node.text:
Sunset flight with the L-39 Albatross.

That’s @inspiration4 Mission Specialist @astrosembro in the backseat, piloted by Doug Demko aka Tut. Thanks to John Baum aka Slick for piloting me in the L-39 and getting me in position for great shots — such an honor to fly with some amazing people.

node.text:
The crew of Inspiration4 poses in the crew access arm at Launch Complex 39A this week.

In 46 days they’ll walk across this arm to begin the trip of a lifetime! 🌎🚀🐉

node.text:
It’s here.

SpaceX’s long-awaited “A Shortfall of Gravitas” droneship has arrived at Port Canaveral in Florida.

That’s one badass-looking rocket landing platform.

node.text:
F L O A T I N G with friends :) — Final zero gravity pic for now, but this time, I’m in it! I think a second or two after this was taken many of us crashed into each other haha. Such an unforgettable experience. Can’t wait to feel weightless again someday 🙂🌎🚀

Thanks @gozerog for capturing this moment and for an awesome flight.
